reviews.text: Food is fine, and value for money.  But service is not so.  Must pay cash.
Standardized food.  Service was good.  Still served customer 5 minutes before closing for dining in.

Decent noodles, reasonable prices, but the space is tiny and crowded, though fortunately, kept clean enough. Part of a chain that originated in the southern HK Island district of Aberdeen, Nam Kee is famous for its signature "spring roll" noodles
Good and cheap comfort food - loads of soup-based noodles to choose from
Good value

reviews.text:
메뉴판을 잘 못읽겟고 ,,,,,장소가 너무 협소하고 사람이 너무많은 시간이라 급하게 골라서 🤞🏻베스트메뉴 1 번? 🤞🏻인가 시켰는데 국물이 🥫토마토 국수인지 ㅜㅜ 시큼하고 맵기만 해서 건더기만 건져먹음..

건더기는 두부껍데기에 싼 어묵 튀긴거에 장조림같은 소고기 토핑이었눈데 넘나 맛남❤️ 국수도 탱글탱글 괜찮았음❤️

국물을 그냥 잘못 골라서 별점 3개 줌 ㅜㅜ엉엉
